Project Overview

This project demonstrates a simple Python program that calculates the sum of two numbers using a user-defined function. It is designed to introduce fundamental programming concepts such as functions, user input, and basic arithmetic operations.

 Problem Statement

Manual calculation can sometimes lead to errors. A simple program is required to:

Accept two numbers from the user
Perform addition using a function
Display the result accurately

 Objectives
Develop a Python program to add two numbers
Understand the use of functions in Python
Learn how to take user input and display output
Perform basic arithmetic operations

 Technologies Used
Programming Language: Python
IDE: VS Code / IDLE

 Features
Accepts user input dynamically
Uses a user-defined function
Performs accurate addition
Simple and beginner-friendly implementation

 How It Works
The program prompts the user to enter two numbers
A function add_numbers(a, b) is defined
The function calculates and returns the sum
The result is displayed to the user


 Algorithm
1. Start
2. Define function add_numbers(a, b)
3. Return a + b
4. Input first number
5. Input second number
6. Call function with inputs
7. Store result
8. Display result
9. End

 Result

The program successfully takes two numbers as input and displays their sum using a Python function.

 Conclusion

This project demonstrates the basic use of functions, user input, and arithmetic operations in Python. It serves as a foundational example for beginners to understand how functions work in real programs.

